text.section:
One of the members shall be an enrolled student in good standing at Montgomery Community College. The student member:
Shall be a resident of Montgomery County;
May not be employed by Montgomery Community College;
Serves for a term of 1 year, beginning July 1 and ending on June 30;
Shall have a cumulative quality point average and a current semester quality point average of at least 2.0;
Shall have successfully completed at least 18 credit hours at Montgomery Community College; and
At the time of appointment and during the term of office, shall be enrolled in at least 6 credit hours at Montgomery Community College.

section.section:
Each member of the Nominating Committee:
Shall be a resident of and a registered voter in Montgomery County;
Shall have a knowledge of and an interest in postsecondary education;
Shall have demonstrated an active interest in civic affairs;
May not be an officer of this State, Montgomery County, or any municipal corporation in Montgomery County or any of their agencies; and
May not be an officer of, employed by, or subject to the authority of Montgomery Community College.
